- 'Audio treasures' refers to public audio files longer than 60 seconds; 
- 'have matured for at least two years' means the upload date is between '2022-01-01' and '2023-12-31'; 
- 'deciphered' means having at least one transcription (i.e., COUNT(tr.transcription_id) > 0); 
- 'audience engagement' means the number of access events (i.e., COUNT(al.access_id)); 
- 'last known contact dates' means the most recent access date (i.e., MAX(al.access_date)); 
- 'clarity of their transcriptions' means the average confidence score of the transcriptions (i.e., AVG(tr.confidence_score)).

- A sample rate of 44100 Hz is commonly used for CD-quality audio; 
- A confidence score measures the accuracy of a transcription, with 1.0 being the highest and 0.0 being the lowest; 
- An average confidence score greater than 0.8 indicates that the transcription is generally accurate.
